        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Instead of implementing ZF-2736 (translation routing), implementing a \"setDefaultLanguage\"-Function would be sufficient.\nI could imagine something like\n\nFile: Zend_Translate_Adapter:\n\npublic function setDefaultLanguage($defaultLanguage)\n{\n    $this->_options['defaultLanguage'] = $defaultLanguage;\n}\n\nAnd in the translation()-Function, insert:\n\nif (isset($this->_options['defaultLanguage']) === true) {\n    return $this->_translate[$this->_options['defaultLanguage']][$messageId];\n}\n\nbelow\n\nif (isset($this->_translate[$locale][$messageId]) === true) {\n    \/\/ return regionless translation (en_US -> en)\n    return $this->_translate[$locale][$messageId];\n}\n\nin order to to support fallbacks....\nIt wouldn't be wrong to check if there's a translation for the fallback language available at all"
        },
